[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:04.410 --> 00:00:14.210 align:middle line:90%


00:00:14.210 --> 00:00:18.100 align:middle line:10%
>> This is Book Tours
and I'm Corinne Edwards.

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:21.160 align:middle line:10%
I'd like you to meet one of the
most important new messengers

00:00:21.160 --> 00:00:22.900 align:middle line:10%
in publishing today.

00:00:22.900 --> 00:00:25.600 align:middle line:84%
Important because the
authors on this show

00:00:25.600 --> 00:00:28.510 align:middle line:84%
are dedicated to helping
your personal growth,

00:00:28.510 --> 00:00:34.010 align:middle line:84%
make you happier, healthier,
to be the best you can be.

00:00:34.010 --> 00:00:36.880 align:middle line:84%
We are delighted to welcome
George Kinder, author

00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:41.450 align:middle line:84%
of "The Seven Stages
of Money Maturity."

00:00:41.450 --> 00:00:44.510 align:middle line:84%
They say money, money, money
makes the world go around,

00:00:44.510 --> 00:00:47.510 align:middle line:84%
but can we embrace
a spiritual life

00:00:47.510 --> 00:00:50.630 align:middle line:84%
and still want to make
lots of that dirty stuff?

00:00:50.630 --> 00:00:53.130 align:middle line:90%
George Kinder says yes.

00:00:53.130 --> 00:00:56.820 align:middle line:84%
George is an internationally
known financial planner,

00:00:56.820 --> 00:01:00.720 align:middle line:90%
and wait, a Buddhist teacher.

00:01:00.720 --> 00:01:03.690 align:middle line:84%
George, I have heard
people say, "I'd

00:01:03.690 --> 00:01:06.960 align:middle line:84%
love to be spiritual but
I have to make a living."

00:01:06.960 --> 00:01:10.465 align:middle line:90%


00:01:10.465 --> 00:01:11.465 align:middle line:90%
What do you think of it?

00:01:11.465 --> 00:01:13.420 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, I think those are--

00:01:13.420 --> 00:01:15.570 align:middle line:10%
that's probably the
most important split

00:01:15.570 --> 00:01:18.700 align:middle line:10%
that we feel in America
today inside of ourselves.

00:01:18.700 --> 00:01:21.390 align:middle line:84%
I think about Thoreau
talking about us all living

00:01:21.390 --> 00:01:24.840 align:middle line:84%
lives of quiet desperation,
and I think that's part of it.

00:01:24.840 --> 00:01:28.470 align:middle line:84%
It's feeling that our spiritual
life is over here someplace,

00:01:28.470 --> 00:01:30.810 align:middle line:90%
and our money life is over here.

00:01:30.810 --> 00:01:33.390 align:middle line:84%
And it's really the reason
that I wrote the book

00:01:33.390 --> 00:01:39.840 align:middle line:84%
because it strikes me that if
we feel that our money life is

00:01:39.840 --> 00:01:43.650 align:middle line:84%
complex and difficult and dark,
and our spiritual life is just

00:01:43.650 --> 00:01:45.600 align:middle line:90%
fine, there's a problem there.

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:50.730 align:middle line:84%
Because money has to do
with how we are articulating

00:01:50.730 --> 00:01:53.310 align:middle line:84%
our soul in the world, how
we are bringing our soul

00:01:53.310 --> 00:01:54.150 align:middle line:90%
into the world.

00:01:54.150 --> 00:01:56.400 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's very important
that we bring these two

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:58.560 align:middle line:84%
worlds together and have
a healthy relationship

00:01:58.560 --> 00:01:59.420 align:middle line:90%
around money.

00:01:59.420 --> 00:02:02.940 align:middle line:84%
>> You are a very important
financial planner and I know

00:02:02.940 --> 00:02:05.940 align:middle line:90%
that you address your peers.

00:02:05.940 --> 00:02:08.820 align:middle line:84%
1,000 financial
advisors at a time.

00:02:08.820 --> 00:02:09.988 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:02:09.988 --> 00:02:13.850 align:middle line:84%
>> What did they say when you
say that it has to do with

00:02:13.850 --> 00:02:14.650 align:middle line:90%
spirituality?

00:02:14.650 --> 00:02:15.960 align:middle line:90%
Do you talk about that to them?

00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:16.430 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, I do.

00:02:16.430 --> 00:02:16.710 align:middle line:90%
I do.

00:02:16.710 --> 00:02:17.835 align:middle line:90%
>> What do you say to them?

00:02:17.835 --> 00:02:21.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I say the same thing
that I just was saying here,

00:02:21.720 --> 00:02:24.900 align:middle line:84%
basically, that as
a financial advisor,

00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:28.140 align:middle line:84%
you have a relationship with
someone sitting in your room.

00:02:28.140 --> 00:02:31.530 align:middle line:84%
And very often, what happens is
that they're sharing something

00:02:31.530 --> 00:02:34.440 align:middle line:84%
with you that they don't
share with their priest

00:02:34.440 --> 00:02:39.390 align:middle line:84%
or with their counselor, they
don't share with other people.

00:02:39.390 --> 00:02:43.770 align:middle line:84%
So there's almost an issue
of taboo around money.

00:02:43.770 --> 00:02:46.500 align:middle line:84%
And you recognize as
a financial advisor

00:02:46.500 --> 00:02:49.470 align:middle line:84%
that there's something
intimate going on in the room.

00:02:49.470 --> 00:02:51.410 align:middle line:90%
What do you do with it?

00:02:51.410 --> 00:02:55.590 align:middle line:84%
If you move back and you
just go to stocks and bonds,

00:02:55.590 --> 00:02:57.020 align:middle line:84%
the person that
you're with is not

00:02:57.020 --> 00:02:58.610 align:middle line:90%
going to feel connected with.

00:02:58.610 --> 00:03:01.910 align:middle line:84%
They aren't going to feel that
the central purpose of money

00:03:01.910 --> 00:03:03.650 align:middle line:84%
in their life is
being addressed.

00:03:03.650 --> 00:03:05.360 align:middle line:84%
And that central
purpose has to do

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:07.940 align:middle line:84%
with what does
freedom mean to you,

00:03:07.940 --> 00:03:10.010 align:middle line:84%
and how can you accomplish
it in the world.

00:03:10.010 --> 00:03:12.427 align:middle line:84%
That's both a spiritual question
and a financial question.

00:03:12.427 --> 00:03:13.802 align:middle line:84%
>> What does
freedom mean to you?

00:03:13.802 --> 00:03:15.385 align:middle line:84%
>> What does
freedom mean to you?

00:03:15.385 --> 00:03:17.940 align:middle line:84%
>> And yet people are so
inhibited about money,

00:03:17.940 --> 00:03:21.400 align:middle line:84%
they say that people will talk
to you about their sex life

00:03:21.400 --> 00:03:23.750 align:middle line:84%
but they will never tell you
how much money they make.

00:03:23.750 --> 00:03:24.920 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, that's right.

00:03:24.920 --> 00:03:26.780 align:middle line:84%
I have a number of
psychologist friends

00:03:26.780 --> 00:03:28.460 align:middle line:84%
who say it's absolutely
the last thing.

00:03:28.460 --> 00:03:30.727 align:middle line:84%
They'll talk about
terrible child abuse,

00:03:30.727 --> 00:03:32.810 align:middle line:84%
they'll talk about their
own personal relationship

00:03:32.810 --> 00:03:35.083 align:middle line:84%
to violence, to
horrible situations,

00:03:35.083 --> 00:03:36.500 align:middle line:84%
and they'll never
mentioned money.

00:03:36.500 --> 00:03:38.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Or a woman will never
tell you how much she weighs.

00:03:38.900 --> 00:03:40.391 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, it's the same thing.

00:03:40.391 --> 00:03:41.480 align:middle line:90%
>> That's the other thing.

00:03:41.480 --> 00:03:42.420 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right, yeah.

00:03:42.420 --> 00:03:45.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Never about money and
never how much she weighs.

00:03:45.220 --> 00:03:47.930 align:middle line:84%
>> The shame about that, the
problem with that really is

00:03:47.930 --> 00:03:50.760 align:middle line:84%
that it means that
money is kind of hiding.

00:03:50.760 --> 00:03:52.970 align:middle line:84%
We're hiding our
lives around money.

00:03:52.970 --> 00:03:54.710 align:middle line:84%
And as a consequence,
when we're not

00:03:54.710 --> 00:03:57.290 align:middle line:84%
finding a way to
deal with it to make

00:03:57.290 --> 00:03:59.630 align:middle line:90%
our lives whole and complete.

00:03:59.630 --> 00:04:01.430 align:middle line:84%
So always, the
spirit's over on one

00:04:01.430 --> 00:04:03.650 align:middle line:84%
side and money's over
on the other side.

00:04:03.650 --> 00:04:04.520 align:middle line:90%
>> There's a shame--

00:04:04.520 --> 00:04:05.555 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:04:05.555 --> 00:04:06.500 align:middle line:90%
>> --about money?

00:04:06.500 --> 00:04:07.490 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:04:07.490 --> 00:04:08.800 align:middle line:90%
>> Why?

00:04:08.800 --> 00:04:12.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Money, you know, there have
been all these surveys about

00:04:12.140 --> 00:04:16.070 align:middle line:84%
money and sex, showing that
the two most frequently thought

00:04:16.070 --> 00:04:16.904 align:middle line:90%
of subjects.

00:04:16.904 --> 00:04:18.529 align:middle line:84%
But you know what,
we think about more,

00:04:18.529 --> 00:04:21.600 align:middle line:84%
we think more about money
than we think about sex

00:04:21.600 --> 00:04:23.370 align:middle line:90%
but we don't talk about it.

00:04:23.370 --> 00:04:26.660 align:middle line:84%
And so a lot of
people feel a sense

00:04:26.660 --> 00:04:29.533 align:middle line:84%
of failure, a sense
of low self-esteem.

00:04:29.533 --> 00:04:30.950 align:middle line:84%
We read in the
Wall Street Journal

00:04:30.950 --> 00:04:34.520 align:middle line:84%
or in the daily paper
about how markets are

00:04:34.520 --> 00:04:36.480 align:middle line:90%
making fortunes for everybody.

00:04:36.480 --> 00:04:39.290 align:middle line:84%
But most of us don't experience
that inside of ourselves

00:04:39.290 --> 00:04:42.650 align:middle line:84%
or we experience how we've lost
money or we failed in business,

00:04:42.650 --> 00:04:45.260 align:middle line:84%
or we experience the
pain of a divorce

00:04:45.260 --> 00:04:47.900 align:middle line:84%
and the financial
consequences of that.

00:04:47.900 --> 00:04:51.170 align:middle line:84%
These are such
circumstances that if we

00:04:51.170 --> 00:04:53.300 align:middle line:84%
don't talk about them, and
if we don't have someone

00:04:53.300 --> 00:04:57.050 align:middle line:84%
that we can trust in relation to
the financial aspects of them,

00:04:57.050 --> 00:04:58.140 align:middle line:90%
we feel very low.

00:04:58.140 --> 00:05:00.530 align:middle line:84%
We feel a lack of
self-esteem and shame

00:05:00.530 --> 00:05:03.080 align:middle line:90%
about our relationship to money.

00:05:03.080 --> 00:05:07.085 align:middle line:84%
>> In recent times, the
stock market has gone crazy.

00:05:07.085 --> 00:05:08.080 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:08.080 --> 00:05:13.850 align:middle line:84%
>> And people I talk to seem
to have so much shame that they

00:05:13.850 --> 00:05:15.710 align:middle line:90%
didn't get in on it.

00:05:15.710 --> 00:05:17.374 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:05:17.374 --> 00:05:20.620 align:middle line:84%
>> And then they have
terrible shame if they sold--

00:05:20.620 --> 00:05:22.322 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yeah.

00:05:22.322 --> 00:05:25.510 align:middle line:84%
>> --before it really
went up very high.

00:05:25.510 --> 00:05:26.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:05:26.310 --> 00:05:31.080 align:middle line:84%
>> And then they have a lot of
shame especially if they sold

00:05:31.080 --> 00:05:32.940 align:middle line:84%
and they lost money
because they panicked.

00:05:32.940 --> 00:05:34.065 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:05:34.065 --> 00:05:37.470 align:middle line:84%
>> How do we get
over this shame?

00:05:37.470 --> 00:05:40.800 align:middle line:84%
>> It's interesting, we
use money to measure.

00:05:40.800 --> 00:05:43.800 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's a measuring
concept how much money we have

00:05:43.800 --> 00:05:46.090 align:middle line:90%
or how much we lose.

00:05:46.090 --> 00:05:48.660 align:middle line:84%
And so we're constantly
measuring ourselves

00:05:48.660 --> 00:05:49.890 align:middle line:90%
against money.

00:05:49.890 --> 00:05:52.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the
important thing and what

00:05:52.020 --> 00:05:54.360 align:middle line:84%
I'm trying to teach
in the book is

00:05:54.360 --> 00:05:57.480 align:middle line:84%
how to come to
terms with and feel

00:05:57.480 --> 00:06:01.150 align:middle line:84%
comfortable with difficult
emotions around money.

00:06:01.150 --> 00:06:04.170 align:middle line:84%
That's really the secret,
is to learn comfortable

00:06:04.170 --> 00:06:07.260 align:middle line:84%
not with the
circumstances but to be

00:06:07.260 --> 00:06:11.640 align:middle line:84%
comfortable with feelings,
to feel at ease with anxiety,

00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:14.300 align:middle line:90%
to feel at ease with shame.

00:06:14.300 --> 00:06:16.290 align:middle line:84%
It's a practice, it's
a spiritual practice

00:06:16.290 --> 00:06:19.590 align:middle line:84%
and a psychological
practice of basically

00:06:19.590 --> 00:06:22.230 align:middle line:84%
of letting our thoughts
go, letting the stories go

00:06:22.230 --> 00:06:24.300 align:middle line:84%
that seemed to trap
us, and learning

00:06:24.300 --> 00:06:26.340 align:middle line:84%
to really feel at
ease in our bodies

00:06:26.340 --> 00:06:27.675 align:middle line:90%
around difficult feelings.

00:06:27.675 --> 00:06:30.032 align:middle line:90%
>> What is money maturity?

00:06:30.032 --> 00:06:32.140 align:middle line:84%
>> Money maturity
involves three things.

00:06:32.140 --> 00:06:37.170 align:middle line:84%
One of them is the
sense of ease or comfort

00:06:37.170 --> 00:06:40.520 align:middle line:84%
in our feelings around
money so that those

00:06:40.520 --> 00:06:42.030 align:middle line:90%
are no longer a problem.

00:06:42.030 --> 00:06:45.170 align:middle line:84%
The second piece of money
maturity is that we have--

00:06:45.170 --> 00:06:48.470 align:middle line:84%
we know that money is
about our aspirations

00:06:48.470 --> 00:06:52.910 align:middle line:84%
and about our freedom, and so
we connect our relationship

00:06:52.910 --> 00:06:55.670 align:middle line:84%
with money to our deepest
places inside of ourselves,

00:06:55.670 --> 00:06:58.640 align:middle line:84%
what's most profound for
us to recognize and realize

00:06:58.640 --> 00:06:59.660 align:middle line:90%
in our lives.

00:06:59.660 --> 00:07:03.110 align:middle line:84%
And then the third thing is to
create a financial plan that

00:07:03.110 --> 00:07:05.840 align:middle line:84%
gets you from A to Z,
basically, that takes you

00:07:05.840 --> 00:07:10.110 align:middle line:84%
from where you are to that
image of freedom or happiness.

00:07:10.110 --> 00:07:12.360 align:middle line:84%
>> You talk about freedom
and you talk about happiness

00:07:12.360 --> 00:07:15.620 align:middle line:84%
but then this book is
not just a holy book.

00:07:15.620 --> 00:07:19.160 align:middle line:84%
This book is a very, very
basic and practical guide.

00:07:19.160 --> 00:07:19.960 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:07:19.960 --> 00:07:24.380 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the startling
things that you say is,

00:07:24.380 --> 00:07:29.930 align:middle line:84%
in your chapter on knowledge,
is to write down how much money

00:07:29.930 --> 00:07:31.640 align:middle line:90%
you need to live.

00:07:31.640 --> 00:07:32.530 align:middle line:90%
Nobody does that.

00:07:32.530 --> 00:07:35.720 align:middle line:90%
>> No, no, no.

00:07:35.720 --> 00:07:37.340 align:middle line:90%
There are so many--

00:07:37.340 --> 00:07:39.650 align:middle line:84%
we have so many emotional
responses to money

00:07:39.650 --> 00:07:41.450 align:middle line:84%
that it's very
difficult for us to take

00:07:41.450 --> 00:07:43.700 align:middle line:84%
on the practical
realities of it.

00:07:43.700 --> 00:07:46.670 align:middle line:84%
And we need to know how
much we need to live.

00:07:46.670 --> 00:07:50.030 align:middle line:84%
We need to know how much
we need to have in order

00:07:50.030 --> 00:07:51.847 align:middle line:84%
to live the life
we want to live,

00:07:51.847 --> 00:07:53.930 align:middle line:84%
in order to accomplish
what we need to accomplish.

00:07:53.930 --> 00:07:56.960 align:middle line:84%
So we need all these practical
things that we have to address.

00:07:56.960 --> 00:08:00.120 align:middle line:84%
>> What does it do for us to
know how much money it costs us

00:08:00.120 --> 00:08:00.920 align:middle line:90%
to live?

00:08:00.920 --> 00:08:03.100 align:middle line:84%
Most of us are scared to
death to write it down.

00:08:03.100 --> 00:08:03.900 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:08:03.900 --> 00:08:06.710 align:middle line:84%
Well, for those people
who are overspending,

00:08:06.710 --> 00:08:11.030 align:middle line:84%
it confronts them with the
fact that they're never

00:08:11.030 --> 00:08:12.860 align:middle line:84%
going to find their
image of freedom

00:08:12.860 --> 00:08:15.200 align:middle line:84%
because they're
constantly overspending.

00:08:15.200 --> 00:08:18.190 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's very important
to face money directly

00:08:18.190 --> 00:08:21.020 align:middle line:84%
as it's important to face
any difficult life situation.

00:08:21.020 --> 00:08:24.050 align:middle line:84%
>> I know you started in the
book telling your story and you

00:08:24.050 --> 00:08:28.250 align:middle line:84%
said that you had, even though
you were a mathematics genius

00:08:28.250 --> 00:08:31.310 align:middle line:84%
it sounds like when you were a
kid and you knew that you had

00:08:31.310 --> 00:08:35.110 align:middle line:90%
this ease with the figures--

00:08:35.110 --> 00:08:37.909 align:middle line:84%
that you were very
loathe to make money.

00:08:37.909 --> 00:08:39.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, I was.

00:08:39.140 --> 00:08:42.730 align:middle line:84%
I actually, in spite of being
very strong in mathematics

00:08:42.730 --> 00:08:46.670 align:middle line:84%
and with money, I ended up
majoring in English Literature.

00:08:46.670 --> 00:08:50.420 align:middle line:84%
And I went out after college
and spent a couple of years

00:08:50.420 --> 00:08:52.460 align:middle line:90%
doing spiritual practices.

00:08:52.460 --> 00:08:58.340 align:middle line:84%
So I felt it inside of
myself, this terrible split

00:08:58.340 --> 00:09:03.410 align:middle line:84%
between money and my
true self in some way.

00:09:03.410 --> 00:09:06.110 align:middle line:84%
And I felt that I didn't
want to go out and have

00:09:06.110 --> 00:09:09.830 align:middle line:84%
to earn a living, but it
felt counterfeit in some way

00:09:09.830 --> 00:09:11.760 align:middle line:84%
to what I really wanted
to do with my life.

00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:13.670 align:middle line:84%
So it's a painful
period in my life.

00:09:13.670 --> 00:09:17.760 align:middle line:84%
And it took me many years of
working as a tax accountant,

00:09:17.760 --> 00:09:20.840 align:middle line:84%
as a financial advisor to
come to terms with that,

00:09:20.840 --> 00:09:24.770 align:middle line:84%
to figure that, in fact, these
two paths of spiritual practice

00:09:24.770 --> 00:09:27.260 align:middle line:84%
and of the financial
reality of life

00:09:27.260 --> 00:09:30.080 align:middle line:84%
are really one
and the same path.

00:09:30.080 --> 00:09:33.230 align:middle line:84%
>> Now when you talk to
these financial advisors,

00:09:33.230 --> 00:09:35.645 align:middle line:84%
what do they say
to you afterwards?

00:09:35.645 --> 00:09:39.940 align:middle line:10%
>> Many of them have, in secret,
been feeling more closely

00:09:39.940 --> 00:09:43.780 align:middle line:10%
aligned with a pastoral
counselor than with a broker

00:09:43.780 --> 00:09:47.480 align:middle line:10%
in their lives because they do
have relationships with people.

00:09:47.480 --> 00:09:53.320 align:middle line:84%
And they are very disappointed,
they're plagued in a way

00:09:53.320 --> 00:09:55.930 align:middle line:84%
by the complexities
that come in,

00:09:55.930 --> 00:09:57.890 align:middle line:84%
the complexities
of people's lives

00:09:57.890 --> 00:09:59.613 align:middle line:84%
and how people
struggle around money.

00:09:59.613 --> 00:10:01.280 align:middle line:84%
And they want to know
how to solve that.

00:10:01.280 --> 00:10:04.630 align:middle line:84%
>> So in a way, you're
feeling of being torn--

00:10:04.630 --> 00:10:05.672 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:10:05.672 --> 00:10:11.240 align:middle line:84%
>> --is how you combined your
practice with your financial

00:10:11.240 --> 00:10:12.040 align:middle line:90%
advice?

00:10:12.040 --> 00:10:12.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:10:12.850 --> 00:10:16.030 align:middle line:84%
>> It's that you are a pastor
and financial advisor all

00:10:16.030 --> 00:10:16.830 align:middle line:90%
at one time.

00:10:16.830 --> 00:10:18.690 align:middle line:84%
>> I do both because
I'm a Buddhist teacher

00:10:18.690 --> 00:10:19.690 align:middle line:90%
and a financial advisor.

00:10:19.690 --> 00:10:20.890 align:middle line:90%
>> I think it's wonderful.

00:10:20.890 --> 00:10:25.780 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about a very
popular subject, and let's

00:10:25.780 --> 00:10:29.350 align:middle line:90%
say it right out loud, money.

00:10:29.350 --> 00:10:32.260 align:middle line:84%
We're talking to George Kinder
about his book, "The Seven

00:10:32.260 --> 00:10:34.240 align:middle line:90%
Stages of Money Maturity".

00:10:34.240 --> 00:10:37.510 align:middle line:84%
Stay with us, you will
recognize yourself here.

