00:10:44.212 --> 00:10:46.210 align:middle line:10%
We're talking to
George Kinder here

00:10:46.210 --> 00:10:49.870 align:middle line:10%
about a very popular
subject, money, and his book.

00:10:49.870 --> 00:10:53.380 align:middle line:10%
It's "The Seven Stages of
Money Maturity, Understanding

00:10:53.380 --> 00:10:57.010 align:middle line:10%
the Spirit and Value
of Money in Your Life".

00:10:57.010 --> 00:11:00.240 align:middle line:84%
OK, what about the
people, George?

00:11:00.240 --> 00:11:04.280 align:middle line:84%
Like a lot of us,
guilty, would say,

00:11:04.280 --> 00:11:07.310 align:middle line:84%
"all my problem is you're going
to be solved anyway because I

00:11:07.310 --> 00:11:08.845 align:middle line:90%
am going to win the lottery."

00:11:08.845 --> 00:11:09.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:11:09.830 --> 00:11:10.070 align:middle line:90%
Well.

00:11:10.070 --> 00:11:12.362 align:middle line:10%
It's something that I call
magical thinking in my book,

00:11:12.362 --> 00:11:13.340 align:middle line:10%
and it's--

00:11:13.340 --> 00:11:15.680 align:middle line:10%
I have seven stages and
the first of those stages

00:11:15.680 --> 00:11:17.240 align:middle line:10%
is a stage I call
innocence, and it

00:11:17.240 --> 00:11:20.060 align:middle line:10%
has to do with our belief
systems around money.

00:11:20.060 --> 00:11:21.680 align:middle line:84%
And this is a common
belief system,

00:11:21.680 --> 00:11:23.450 align:middle line:90%
more common than it should be.

00:11:23.450 --> 00:11:25.250 align:middle line:84%
And what happens
is that if we buy

00:11:25.250 --> 00:11:30.230 align:middle line:84%
into that kind of belief
system, it robs us

00:11:30.230 --> 00:11:32.510 align:middle line:90%
of other energies inside of us.

00:11:32.510 --> 00:11:34.730 align:middle line:84%
It robs us, for
instance, of our vigor

00:11:34.730 --> 00:11:36.950 align:middle line:84%
so that we can pursue
what it is that we really

00:11:36.950 --> 00:11:39.180 align:middle line:90%
want to accomplish in life.

00:11:39.180 --> 00:11:42.920 align:middle line:84%
So these belief
systems are things

00:11:42.920 --> 00:11:48.860 align:middle line:84%
that I teach how to be more
relaxed around so that we are

00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:51.890 align:middle line:84%
not so attached to them, so that
we recognize them as just one

00:11:51.890 --> 00:11:52.960 align:middle line:90%
possibility of many.

00:11:52.960 --> 00:11:55.385 align:middle line:84%
>> So we don't stop
buying lottery tickets?

00:11:55.385 --> 00:11:57.185 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, I--

00:11:57.185 --> 00:11:58.280 align:middle line:90%
>> Do you buy them?

00:11:58.280 --> 00:11:59.360 align:middle line:90%
>> No, I don't.

00:11:59.360 --> 00:12:01.430 align:middle line:84%
I did years ago,
but I don't anymore.

00:12:01.430 --> 00:12:06.860 align:middle line:84%
[LAUGHS] And the reason is
that saving and investing

00:12:06.860 --> 00:12:10.280 align:middle line:84%
is a very powerful tool
for becoming frayed.

00:12:10.280 --> 00:12:14.180 align:middle line:84%
Do you know that if you
put $2,000 in an IRA

00:12:14.180 --> 00:12:19.580 align:middle line:84%
but you destined it for your
daughter or your granddaughter

00:12:19.580 --> 00:12:22.795 align:middle line:84%
when she is born, that at
the time of retirement,

00:12:22.795 --> 00:12:24.920 align:middle line:84%
if you had invested that
money in the stock market,

00:12:24.920 --> 00:12:27.045 align:middle line:84%
that money would be worth
between $1 and $2 million

00:12:27.045 --> 00:12:27.920 align:middle line:90%
for that child?

00:12:27.920 --> 00:12:28.720 align:middle line:90%
>> Wow.

00:12:28.720 --> 00:12:32.870 align:middle line:84%
>> So compounding at a stock
market rate of return is a very

00:12:32.870 --> 00:12:36.380 align:middle line:90%
powerful way to become wealthy.

00:12:36.380 --> 00:12:41.090 align:middle line:84%
>> The biggest problem I have
found with most people is--

00:12:41.090 --> 00:12:43.580 align:middle line:90%
and the conversations I hear--

00:12:43.580 --> 00:12:47.600 align:middle line:84%
is that when they get
any kind of a windfall,

00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:52.210 align:middle line:84%
they feel obligated to some
reason to spend it right away.

00:12:52.210 --> 00:12:53.590 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:12:53.590 --> 00:12:56.180 align:middle line:90%
>> It comes in different ways.

00:12:56.180 --> 00:12:58.880 align:middle line:84%
Most for the most part, it's
because they feel deprived.

00:12:58.880 --> 00:13:00.590 align:middle line:90%
They felt deprived in some way.

00:13:00.590 --> 00:13:04.280 align:middle line:84%
They've had visions or
fantasies of the perfect life

00:13:04.280 --> 00:13:06.450 align:middle line:90%
and they've never had it.

00:13:06.450 --> 00:13:09.350 align:middle line:84%
And this happens not
merely with sudden wealth

00:13:09.350 --> 00:13:11.974 align:middle line:84%
in terms of winning lottery,
but in terms of divorce.

00:13:11.974 --> 00:13:12.740 align:middle line:90%
>> With people on commission.

00:13:12.740 --> 00:13:14.198 align:middle line:84%
People who work on
commission, they

00:13:14.198 --> 00:13:15.930 align:middle line:90%
get all of a sudden a big check.

00:13:15.930 --> 00:13:16.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:13:16.220 --> 00:13:18.595 align:middle line:84%
>> They don't know where their
next check is coming from,

00:13:18.595 --> 00:13:20.930 align:middle line:90%
but they have this one, $10,000.

00:13:20.930 --> 00:13:21.860 align:middle line:90%
What can we buy?

00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:24.500 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, the other problem
with this, Corinne,

00:13:24.500 --> 00:13:29.490 align:middle line:84%
is that they have no vision
of what their future might be.

00:13:29.490 --> 00:13:31.220 align:middle line:84%
In other words,
financial planning

00:13:31.220 --> 00:13:34.520 align:middle line:84%
is something that looks at our
lives over time in relation

00:13:34.520 --> 00:13:35.380 align:middle line:90%
to money.

00:13:35.380 --> 00:13:38.450 align:middle line:84%
And it takes our lives
seriously over time.

00:13:38.450 --> 00:13:40.850 align:middle line:90%
What do we want to accomplish?

00:13:40.850 --> 00:13:43.100 align:middle line:84%
How much can we
give to the world?

00:13:43.100 --> 00:13:45.380 align:middle line:90%
How much can we grow?

00:13:45.380 --> 00:13:49.610 align:middle line:84%
How deeply profoundly can we
express ourselves over time?

00:13:49.610 --> 00:13:51.950 align:middle line:84%
What happens is people are
so caught up in the moment

00:13:51.950 --> 00:13:53.630 align:middle line:84%
and they feel so
deprived for not

00:13:53.630 --> 00:13:55.640 align:middle line:84%
having had this
money in the past,

00:13:55.640 --> 00:13:57.080 align:middle line:90%
that they spend it very quickly.

00:13:57.080 --> 00:13:59.480 align:middle line:84%
I see it with people who
come through divorces

00:13:59.480 --> 00:14:04.250 align:middle line:84%
and feel devastated from the
divorce and feel very scared.

00:14:04.250 --> 00:14:07.730 align:middle line:84%
So their self-esteem is very
low and they can spend down

00:14:07.730 --> 00:14:09.670 align:middle line:84%
whatever they've
received in a divorce

00:14:09.670 --> 00:14:11.200 align:middle line:90%
in very short period of time.

00:14:11.200 --> 00:14:13.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think it's a
symptom of depression?

00:14:13.270 --> 00:14:15.590 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that that's
part of it, yeah.

00:14:15.590 --> 00:14:18.800 align:middle line:84%
There's a certain despair
about not having money,

00:14:18.800 --> 00:14:22.200 align:middle line:84%
about not being wealthy
that people feel,

00:14:22.200 --> 00:14:23.390 align:middle line:90%
and they can't stand it.

00:14:23.390 --> 00:14:25.220 align:middle line:84%
So when they get the
money, they don't want

00:14:25.220 --> 00:14:26.927 align:middle line:90%
to delay their gratification.

00:14:26.927 --> 00:14:28.385 align:middle line:84%
They want to have
it all right now.

00:14:28.385 --> 00:14:32.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think it's because
they feel that there's more

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:34.090 align:middle line:90%
money right around the corner?

00:14:34.090 --> 00:14:36.442 align:middle line:84%
>> There may be some
fantasy in that regard,

00:14:36.442 --> 00:14:38.900 align:middle line:84%
but I think they don't really
want to look at what's coming

00:14:38.900 --> 00:14:40.570 align:middle line:90%
right around the corner.

00:14:40.570 --> 00:14:43.070 align:middle line:84%
Because if they did, they'd see
that the money is all going.

00:14:43.070 --> 00:14:45.110 align:middle line:84%
>> And they're going to
put some of it away anyway.

00:14:45.110 --> 00:14:45.910 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:14:45.910 --> 00:14:47.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Is it OK to spend some?

00:14:47.270 --> 00:14:48.440 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, sure.

00:14:48.440 --> 00:14:50.810 align:middle line:84%
I think it's important to
spend some of those times.

00:14:50.810 --> 00:14:54.350 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a whole thing in
the new age community that says

00:14:54.350 --> 00:14:58.160 align:middle line:84%
the reason you don't have money
is because you have not opened

00:14:58.160 --> 00:15:00.590 align:middle line:90%
yourself to abundance.

00:15:00.590 --> 00:15:03.192 align:middle line:90%
You have not let it flow.

00:15:03.192 --> 00:15:04.400 align:middle line:90%
What do you think about that?

00:15:04.400 --> 00:15:08.000 align:middle line:84%
>> I think that that's
another innocent notion.

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:10.730 align:middle line:84%
I think that that's
true for some people

00:15:10.730 --> 00:15:12.540 align:middle line:84%
and that's helpful
for some people.

00:15:12.540 --> 00:15:15.260 align:middle line:84%
But for many people, it's
just not appropriate.

00:15:15.260 --> 00:15:16.850 align:middle line:84%
Because our
relationship to money

00:15:16.850 --> 00:15:19.340 align:middle line:84%
involves really knowing
what money is about,

00:15:19.340 --> 00:15:23.300 align:middle line:84%
thinking about our future,
saving, investing, planning.

00:15:23.300 --> 00:15:26.398 align:middle line:84%
So there's a lot of very
practical kind of earthy things

00:15:26.398 --> 00:15:27.815 align:middle line:84%
that have to be
done around money.

00:15:27.815 --> 00:15:29.410 align:middle line:90%
>> Are they spiritual?

00:15:29.410 --> 00:15:32.250 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think they
think that they are,

00:15:32.250 --> 00:15:34.750 align:middle line:84%
I think that this is a
spiritual relationship to money.

00:15:34.750 --> 00:15:39.940 align:middle line:84%
But you know, the spirit
is part of our heart,

00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:41.950 align:middle line:84%
and it's part of the
energy of our body,

00:15:41.950 --> 00:15:43.060 align:middle line:90%
and it's part of our mind.

00:15:43.060 --> 00:15:45.610 align:middle line:84%
There are all of these
different forces that

00:15:45.610 --> 00:15:48.220 align:middle line:84%
have to be engaged
with in relation

00:15:48.220 --> 00:15:49.980 align:middle line:84%
to money and in
relation to the spirit.

00:15:49.980 --> 00:15:52.900 align:middle line:84%
And so it's not just a
simple pat phrase like money

00:15:52.900 --> 00:15:55.090 align:middle line:84%
it's about abundance or
money is about prosperity

00:15:55.090 --> 00:15:56.950 align:middle line:90%
and just open to the flow.

00:15:56.950 --> 00:15:58.960 align:middle line:84%
I had a fellow who opened
to the flow like that.

00:15:58.960 --> 00:16:00.870 align:middle line:90%
That was his notion.

00:16:00.870 --> 00:16:03.490 align:middle line:84%
And he lived a wonderful
life for many years

00:16:03.490 --> 00:16:06.400 align:middle line:84%
and then he discovered that
these heart palpitations

00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:08.920 align:middle line:84%
that he had were in fact
symptoms of something much more

00:16:08.920 --> 00:16:09.910 align:middle line:90%
serious.

00:16:09.910 --> 00:16:12.340 align:middle line:84%
And he had three daughters
who needed to be educated

00:16:12.340 --> 00:16:14.483 align:middle line:84%
and had not saved
a dime in his life

00:16:14.483 --> 00:16:16.150 align:middle line:84%
and he was concerned
about their legacy.

00:16:16.150 --> 00:16:19.150 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, that
whole world kind of

00:16:19.150 --> 00:16:21.130 align:middle line:84%
blew up for him as
he realized that he

00:16:21.130 --> 00:16:23.290 align:middle line:84%
needed to address
money, I think,

00:16:23.290 --> 00:16:25.921 align:middle line:90%
in a much more adult way.

00:16:25.921 --> 00:16:28.490 align:middle line:84%
>> So we don't trust
like Gandhi did.

00:16:28.490 --> 00:16:30.740 align:middle line:84%
We don't trust like
St. Francis of Assisi.

00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:34.020 align:middle line:84%
We don't trust like in the
Bible or lilies of the field.

00:16:34.020 --> 00:16:37.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Oh, I think that trust is a
lovely thing and I think that

00:16:37.340 --> 00:16:40.640 align:middle line:84%
Francis of Assisi and Gandhi
were very mature around money.

00:16:40.640 --> 00:16:44.960 align:middle line:84%
But it takes a quality
of extraordinary depth

00:16:44.960 --> 00:16:48.230 align:middle line:84%
to take a vow of
poverty as Francis did.

00:16:48.230 --> 00:16:51.240 align:middle line:84%
Most of us have this
image of having the flow

00:16:51.240 --> 00:16:54.500 align:middle line:84%
but we don't really
look at what it means.

00:16:54.500 --> 00:16:56.610 align:middle line:84%
Francis did look
at what it meant

00:16:56.610 --> 00:16:59.600 align:middle line:84%
and what the consequences of
that would mean for his life.

00:16:59.600 --> 00:17:01.925 align:middle line:84%
And he died a very
young man as well.

00:17:01.925 --> 00:17:02.930 align:middle line:90%
>> Because he was broke?

00:17:02.930 --> 00:17:05.240 align:middle line:90%
>> Because he didn't--

00:17:05.240 --> 00:17:08.960 align:middle line:84%
I think, probably, he didn't
take care enough of his body.

00:17:08.960 --> 00:17:10.889 align:middle line:84%
He lived in very
poor circumstances.

00:17:10.889 --> 00:17:15.220 align:middle line:84%
>> What about people who go the
other extreme and they save,

00:17:15.220 --> 00:17:18.690 align:middle line:84%
save, save, save, save toward
their retirement and live poor?

00:17:18.690 --> 00:17:21.579 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, that's very
sad too, isn't it?

00:17:21.579 --> 00:17:24.839 align:middle line:84%
Again, I think that
the important thing

00:17:24.839 --> 00:17:27.900 align:middle line:84%
in money maturity is knowing
what freedom means for you.

00:17:27.900 --> 00:17:30.380 align:middle line:84%
It's not just saving
for retirement.

00:17:30.380 --> 00:17:31.380 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe in that.

00:17:31.380 --> 00:17:33.900 align:middle line:84%
I think that money
is really about what

00:17:33.900 --> 00:17:36.480 align:middle line:84%
is freedom, what is
happiness for us,

00:17:36.480 --> 00:17:39.210 align:middle line:84%
and how can we use money
and the forces of the world

00:17:39.210 --> 00:17:41.300 align:middle line:90%
to accomplish it.

00:17:41.300 --> 00:17:43.550 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's the
question that really needs

00:17:43.550 --> 00:17:45.680 align:middle line:84%
to be addressed,
whether you save a lot

00:17:45.680 --> 00:17:48.420 align:middle line:84%
or you just are working
with money as a flow.

00:17:48.420 --> 00:17:50.230 align:middle line:84%
>> You know one
of the tips that--

00:17:50.230 --> 00:17:52.400 align:middle line:84%
all through the
book, you give tips.

00:17:52.400 --> 00:17:55.430 align:middle line:84%
Very practical tips that
are not very spiritual.

00:17:55.430 --> 00:18:00.920 align:middle line:84%
Like it is not holy to pay
the IRS too much money.

00:18:00.920 --> 00:18:01.905 align:middle line:90%
Keep your receipts.

00:18:01.905 --> 00:18:02.705 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:18:02.705 --> 00:18:03.720 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS] Yes.

00:18:03.720 --> 00:18:07.580 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, every receipt
for $20, you say,

00:18:07.580 --> 00:18:08.820 align:middle line:90%
is worth $5 to you.

00:18:08.820 --> 00:18:09.620 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:18:09.620 --> 00:18:10.460 align:middle line:90%
>> Would you throw it away?

00:18:10.460 --> 00:18:11.530 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yeah.

00:18:11.530 --> 00:18:12.770 align:middle line:90%
>> And we don't do that.

00:18:12.770 --> 00:18:15.520 align:middle line:84%
We say, "oh well,
that's not necessary."

00:18:15.520 --> 00:18:17.620 align:middle line:84%
The cab driver went on a
business trip in Canberra

00:18:17.620 --> 00:18:18.912 align:middle line:90%
and said, "you want a receipt?"

00:18:18.912 --> 00:18:22.060 align:middle line:84%
"No, it's all right, it's
only $20, it's only $25."

00:18:22.060 --> 00:18:23.770 align:middle line:90%
But you say be careful.

00:18:23.770 --> 00:18:26.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, yeah, I mean, that's--

00:18:26.470 --> 00:18:28.150 align:middle line:84%
one of my friends
calls that energy

00:18:28.150 --> 00:18:31.720 align:middle line:84%
leakage that you can lose a
lot by not paying attention

00:18:31.720 --> 00:18:32.710 align:middle line:90%
to these things.

00:18:32.710 --> 00:18:36.280 align:middle line:84%
Money requires attention just
as a garden requires attention.

00:18:36.280 --> 00:18:40.360 align:middle line:84%
It requires careful
weeding, it requires

00:18:40.360 --> 00:18:43.800 align:middle line:84%
proper watering and one needs
to know the season of it.

00:18:43.800 --> 00:18:47.440 align:middle line:84%
So these practical tips like
paying attention to taxes

00:18:47.440 --> 00:18:49.630 align:middle line:84%
and paying attention
to your investments

00:18:49.630 --> 00:18:52.290 align:middle line:84%
and having an appropriate
relationship to savings

00:18:52.290 --> 00:18:55.960 align:middle line:84%
are critical if you're going
to achieve the kind of life

00:18:55.960 --> 00:18:57.295 align:middle line:90%
that you want to achieve.

00:18:57.295 --> 00:19:01.450 align:middle line:84%
>> And of course, the big thing
that strikes terror in all

00:19:01.450 --> 00:19:06.140 align:middle line:84%
of our breasts is you say get
rid of the credit card debt.

00:19:06.140 --> 00:19:08.192 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, yeah, so--

00:19:08.192 --> 00:19:09.400 align:middle line:90%
>> How do we live without it?

00:19:09.400 --> 00:19:14.620 align:middle line:84%
>> [LAUGHS] Well, so many
people that I see that come

00:19:14.620 --> 00:19:16.990 align:middle line:84%
into my office have
an excess of debt.

00:19:16.990 --> 00:19:20.890 align:middle line:84%
And as a consequence, they
don't have a very positive image

00:19:20.890 --> 00:19:23.800 align:middle line:84%
